        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
<parametername>:</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_v__csc" kindref="compound">XV_csc</ref> instance to be initialized. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
<parametername>:</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Base address of the device to be looked up and initialized.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
This function looks up the configuration for a device using the provided base address, and then initializes the <ref refid="struct_x_v__csc" kindref="compound">XV_csc</ref> instance with the found configuration. If the configuration cannot be found, the function sets the instance&apos;s IsReady flag to 0 and returns XST_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND.</para><para><simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if initialization was successful.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND if the device configuration could not be found. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
